1. **Error Handling**:
```javascript
async function getUser(id) {
  try {
    const response = await fetch(`/api/users/${id}`);
    if (!response.ok) {
      throw new Error(`HTTP error! status: ${response.status}`);
    }
    return response.json();
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error fetching user:', error);
    throw error;
  }
}
```
In this improved version, we use a `try-catch` block to catch any errors that occur during the fetch operation. We also check the HTTP status code of the response to determine if it's an error.

